{Mar del Plata (15-31 iii) 1934 was the fourth championship of South America.
Fourteen men participated. The tournament became a race between the
Argentinians Schwartzman and Grau.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nc3 d5 4. Nf3 Nbd7 5.
cxd5 exd5 6. Bf4 c6 7. e3 Nh5 8. Be2 $5 ({Theory is} 8. Bg5 $1 Be7 9. Bxe7 Qxe7
10. Be2 {(Saemisch - Spielmann, Wiesbaden 1925).}) 8... Nxf4 9. exf4 Bd6 10. g3
O-O 11. O-O Re8 12. Bd3 Nf8 13. Qc2 f6 $5 (13... Bg4 $1 14. Ne5 Bh5 {
gains a plus.}) 14. f5 $1 {Schwartzman has a pawn storm in mind.} Bd7 15. a3
Re7 16. Rfe1 Be8 17. Rxe7 Qxe7 18. g4 Bf7 19. Re1 Qd8 $5 20. Na4 h5 $5 21. h3
hxg4 22. hxg4 Rc8 $5 23. Nc5 Bb8 24. Qd2 ({Not} 24. Nxb7 $4 Qc7 25. Nc5 Qf4 {
(Lachaga).}) 24... b6 25. Ne6 $5 {White makes a valiant attempt.} Qd6 $1 {
Black defends well.} 26. g5 $5 Bh5 $6 (26... Re8 $1 27. gxf6 Nxe6 28. fxe6 Rxe6
29. fxg7 Qf4 $1 {leads to a positional edge for Black.}) 27. Qe3 Re8 $2 {
Bolbochan misses the proper defence.} (27... Qe7 $1 28. Nxf8 Qxe3 29. fxe3 $1
Rxf8 30. Kf2 {brings equality.}) 28. gxf6 $1 Bxf3 ({The pointe is} 28... gxf6
29. Qh6 $1) 29. Qxf3 Nxe6 {Black cannot deliver mate in one.} 30. fxe6 gxf6 31.
Bh7+ $1 Kg7 ({Or} 31... Kxh7 32. Qh5+ Kg7 33. Qf7+ $1 Kh6 34. Qxf6+ Kh5 35.
Re5+ {(Lachaga).}) 32. Qg4+ Kh8 33. Bg6 Qh2+ 34. Kf1 Re7 35. Re3 Qh1+ 36. Ke2
Qc1 37. Qh5+ {White will mate soon.} 1-0

