Piazzini won. Number six became Mar del Plata (12-31 iii) 1936. Sixteen
players participated. Pleci and Schwartzman shared the lead, when the last
round began. It became an exciting finish.} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 Bg7 4.
Nf3 d6 5. e4 Nc6 6. Bg5 $5 h6 7. Bf4 Bg4 8. Be2 Bxf3 9. gxf3 $5 {
It is wiser to capture with a bishop.} e5 10. Be3 $5 exd4 11. Bxd4 Nxd4 12.
Qxd4 O-O $5 13. Qd2 Nd7 14. Nd5 $5 Nc5 15. Rb1 $6 a5 $1 {
Black has gained a positional edge.} 16. b3 c6 17. Ne3 Qf6 18. Ng4 Qg5 $1 19.
Qxd6 $5 Rfd8 20. Qg3 $2 ({Correct is} 20. h4 $1 Rxd6 21. hxg5 hxg5 {
and Black has  a plus.}) 20... Qd2+ $1 21. Kf1 Qxa2 22. Re1 Qxb3 {
Pleci has a lost game.} 23. Qf4 h5 24. Nh6+ Bxh6 25. Qxh6 Qc3 $5 26. Rg1 Qg7 $6
{Black should advance the a-pawn.} 27. Qe3 Ne6 $2 {
Villegas fails to decide the game.} ({Right is} 27... Qd4 $1) 28. f4 $1 Qh6 29.
f5 Qxe3 30. fxe3 Ng7 31. fxg6 fxg6 32. Rxg6 Re8 $5 33. Kf2 $5 Re5 $2 {
Pleci gets a fine chance.} (33... Rxe4 34. Reg1 Rf8+ 35. Bf3 {(Lachaga)} Rg4
36. R1xg4 hxg4 37. Rxg4 a4 {keeps an advantage.}) 34. Reg1 $1 Rf8+ 35. Bf3 Rf7
36. R1g5 Rxg5 37. Rxg5 b6 38. Rg6 Rc7 39. e5 $1 Kf7 $2 (39... b5 $1 40. cxb5
cxb5 41. Bd5+ Kf8 {gives survival chances.}) 40. Rf6+ Ke7 41. Bxc6 a4 42. Bxa4
Rc5 43. Rxb6 Rxe5 44. Bc2 Ne6 45. Kf3 Kf6 46. h4 Rc5 47. Bd3 Re5 48. Be4 Ke7
49. Bd5 Nc5 50. e4 Kd7 51. Rh6 Nd3 52. Ke3 Ne1 53. c5 Ng2+ 54. Kd4 Re7 55. Rxh5
Nf4 56. Rh6 Ne2+ 57. Kc4 Ng3 58. Ra6 Re5 59. Kd4 Rh5 60. c6+ {
Pleci won the game after great difficulties.} 1-0

